HEADWORD: Roquelaure
<hw>Roq"ue*laure</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.; so
called after Duc de <etsep>Roquelaure</etsep>, in the reign of Louis
XIV.]</ety> <def>A cloak reaching about to, or just below, the knees,
worn in the 18th century.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>roquelo</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

